<br>
I haven't used it in ages, don't need it for taunt and can't think of another reason to use it.<br>
<br>
To those that said &quot;raise it 50 pts, allow it to work on magical weapons, etc.&quot; I disagree.  Not every ability or skill has to be hugely beneficial, and I think this is a perfect example.  It's not like it costs you anything to mash the key, it's not like you spent AA points on it or it is hugely effective for some other class but not ours.  It's just a minor ability that does a minor thing.  Useful trick for PvP/duels, although if the person is paying attention it's still just a minor annoyance to put the weapon back on.<br>
<br>
Regarding the &quot;magic&quot; restriction, I'm pretty sure that's in place mostly to keep disarmers from ninja looting good weapons, the same way rogues can't pickpocket magic items.  Although I suppose you could try to disarm the Statue of Rallos Zek to get his Reaver... <p><BR>
