<br>
I actually wouldn't be surprised if there was a level cap of some sort on Disarm, since many other abilities like Stun and Taunt have level caps, so Disarming any uber mob even if they have a non-Magic weapon might be a waste of time.  But again, it doesn't cost you anything especially if you macro it to some other action you're mashing the key for anyway. <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a>
<BR>
60 Crusader
<BR>
Reign in Power
<BR>
Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=normandy>Normandy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 224<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/4/02 4:52:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15149.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disarm</span><hr size=1> Disarm has a number of non-intuitive uses.<br>
<br>
When I'm pulling to help PL guildmates or friends, I often run up to a mob and use Disarm to aggro it.  It uses zero mana (unlike pulling with stuns), and produces aggro 100% of the time (unlike Taunt), while inducing zero damage on the mob (so I won't accidentally KS a greenie).  Plus it can be used on the run without pausing to cast.<br>
<br>
Also, there are places where it's hard to pull a mob any other way, such as when they're up on a ledge and you can't smack them, or stun-pull (&quot;you can't see your target&quot;).  Run up to just under them and Disarm+Taunt, it'll aggro them more often than not.<br>
<br>
Plus, I'm pretty sure it helps maintain aggro while tanking.<br>
